A former FCT Minister, Senator Adamu Aliero, of the All Progressives Congress (APC) has won Kebbi Central Senatorial election. The Returning Officer, Professor Kasimu Shehu, said Aliero got 232,000 votes to win the poll. He said Shehu Abubakar (GEDA) of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) came second with 75,638 votes. The senatorial zone is made up of Aliero, Gwandu, Jega, Bunza, Koko/Besse, Kalgo, Birnin Kebbi and Maiyama local government areas of Kebbi state. Aliero seeks 3rd term in Senate Aliero wins Kebbi Central senatorial primary Senatorial primary: Na'Allah wins APC ticket